criteria.textblock:
        Inclusion Criteria:

          -  Speak English or attend with a translator;

          -  ≥ 60 years;

          -  FRAIL scale score ≥1;

          -  Have ≥1 diagnosed chronic condition (i.e., diabetes, obesity, cancer (other than minor
             skin cancer), chronic lung disease, cardiovascular disease, congestive heart failure,
             hypertension, osteoporosis, arthritis, stroke, or kidney disease).

        Exclusion Criteria:

          -  Currently doing similar resistance exercise ≥2x/week;

          -  In palliative care;

          -  Not able to perform basic activities of daily living;

          -  Cognitive impairment (e.g., unable to follow two-step commands);

          -  Travelling >1 week during exposure;

          -  Absolute exercise contraindications (i.e., if they select "no" to any question in the
             Get Active Questionnaire they must seek physician approval before exercising)
